abstract: The lender sold 51 percent of the Czech business, recently renamed Moneta Money Bank, in an offering on the Prague Stock Exchange.
snippet: The lender sold 51 percent of the Czech business, recently renamed Moneta Money Bank, in an offering on the Prague Stock Exchange.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Moneta Money Bank, the banking business of GE Capital in the Czech Republic, said on Friday that it was valued at 34.7 billion Czech korunas, or about $1.5 billion, in its initial public offering in Prague.

headline.main: GE Capital’s Czech Bank Valued at $1.5 Billion in I.P.O.
